animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Antonia was rescued from a rescue partner in Texas. She was pregnant when rescued and arrived to her foster in West Virginia on December 12th. Just in time too, because she started giving birth on December 16th! She will be available for adoption after her puppies are weaned. She is HW+ and will be treated at SSR's expense. Continue to check back in for updates.

Antonia has begun to open up more since being with us. We will have a better idea of her personality once the puppies have been separated from her. Currently, we know that she is a super sweet girl. She can be very submissive especially to men. She loves to play with toys, but you cannot leave her unattended with them because she enjoys eating them as well. Antonia hates bath time. This is something that she will need help with. She is terrified of the shower. She does pretty well on the leash, she does pull a little bit, but with more practice she would be awesome on a leash. She is very food driven and she is house trained! She has been staying in a large outdoor kennel in our basement with the puppies. We have not crate tested her yet, but I think she would be fine. She does well with other dogs. She has not been cat tested yet. She seems to be fine with kids, but can be a little uneasy, so older kids or dog savvy kids would probably be best. This is all also based off of her being around her puppies. I'm sure once she is away from them she will become more relaxed and not feel the need to protect them. She is so sweet and loves to sit by you and cuddle. She currently does not get up on our furniture no matter how much I try to convince her. A lowkey environment would probably be best for her. We will continue to update this as we learn more about her.If you are an approved adopter and are interested in this dog, please let your case worker know. If you are not yet an approved adopter but are interested, please complete an adoption application!
You can review our adoption process, www.shenandoahrescue.org/adoption-process if interested. Donations can be made at shenandoahrescue.org/donate or on PayPal to info@shenandoahrescue.org

animal.description:
Hi, I'm 'Lil Bean! My snaggle teeth and my underbite are hard to not fall in love with. When I'm feeling particularly happy I like to throw myself to the ground and flail around on my back like a maniac! My foster mom picked me up from Animal Control so my background is a mystery.

I am completely potty trained, I have never had an accident in my foster home. I am totally content in my kennel when my foster mom is home and she says I need a time out. I do have some separation anxiety, so being alone in my kennel when my foster mom is not home is a bit stressful for me. My foster mom does have to puppy proof before she leaves because I do get a little anxious, but we are working on it. At night I snuggle up real close with my foster mom, she says I'm the best snuggler! I love it so much some mornings she has to bribe me out of bed!

I am really good at sit, stay and 'look at me.' I am a fast learner and will do just about anything for a treat! Because of the pandemic, regular classes aren't really in the cards for me, but I have met with a trainer and a behaviorist, and they've given my mom some great tools and routines to work on to help me with my confidence out in the world. We are working on my manners. We play fun games that are helping build my confidence and that can be used as distraction tools when I need to be redirected. I have issues with reactivity when seeing other dogs when I'm out and about. We are working hard on this, and I would need someone willing to diligently continue this training. I am starting some new medications that will hopefully calm me a little to help with my separation anxiety and dog reactivity. One day my mom took me to the salon she works at and I got to meet so many people, I was a huge hit! I might not ever be a dog that can go to the dog park or be a patio dog, but I make up for in how much I love my humans.

I haven't had much interaction with kids, but probably wouldn't do well with real little ones till I learned my manners a little better. I just get very excited for new people and get a little jumpy, plus everyone tells me I have a whip for a tail! I'm not sure how I'd do with cats, I saw one once on a walk and wasn't overly interested, and I don't show much interest in all the little animals that come eat at my moms sliding glass door. I am the kind of girl that would need to be the only dog in the house, and would need ongoing work with my excitement level when I see other dogs.

I am a very eager to please girl that just wants to snuggle and be loved. I love my walks just as much as I love my naps. Can't wait to meet you!
animal.name: Lil' Bean

Hello.  Meet  Hairy Paw-ter.  I was a stray that was not claimed.  We are unsure of his breed but we uploaded his pictures in our scanner application and it says American Bulldog with American Staffordshire Terrier. He is young around 9 months-1 1/2 years of age.  When he first arrived, we realized that he had very little training.  We have been working on him with leash training and the "Sit" command.  He can be a stubborn boy but he is learning!!!  Training will need to continue after his adoption.  He keeps his kennel clean during the day but occasionally has accidents at night.  He has been good with some dogs but isn't always sure about super dominant dogs.  Overall just a work in progress but he is turning into a great dog a little more each day.  A fenced yard is a must as he is very athletic and needs a safe place to exercise.  An active family would be great as well.  The adoption fee is $160.00.

If you are interested in adopting please fill out our short Adoption Application to start the adoption process. An adoption application can be completed & submitted on our website yorkadoptapet.com or picked up at the shelter (1511 North Platte, York, NE) during open hours, Tuesday-Saturday, Noon-3pm. For more information on any of the dogs available for adoption contact kim@yorkadoptapet.com. All applications need to be approved prior to adoption and approval may take up to 1 week.

The stray hold, at the Toccoa-Stephens County Humane Shelter, is 5 days. That allows owners a fair amount of time to come looking for their pets. On the sixth day, the animal becomes the property of the Toccoa-Stephens County Humane Shelter and is offered for adoption. An animal may be pre-adopted, however, if the owner comes forward, within the 5 day stray hold, the animal goes back to the owner. The adoption fee is refunded at that time.

Adoption Fees: Adoption fee includes spay or neuter, current (age appropriate) vaccinations, and a microchip.

animal.description:
Meet Tobee! Tobee is currently enrolled in the P.A.C.K. Program, a 9 week intensive program for routine obedience, agility, and handling training with a prison inmate trainer and he is almost ready to show off all that he has learned to new adopters. His new skills include 'sit', 'stay', 'down', 'place', 'shake' and more! New adopters should realize that PACK Program graduates will require regular, ongoing reinforcement of learned behaviors in order for them to become permanent.
Tobee went in to the PACK Program as a wild child and has made huge strides while there. His handler reports that he has come a very long way in a short period of time and has a calmer state of mind all around. He can be a bit stubborn, they say. So an adopter that is willing and able to be firm and consistent will be key in his continued success. Tobee does well overall with the other dogs in the program, but his energy level while playing can skyrocket and he will become vocal and mouthy. He would enjoy having a dog friend, but monitored playtime until you get to know him will be necessary. Tobee should not go to a home with small dogs or cats. He is house trained and crate trained. He is sweet and friendly, and has all the potential to make some lucky soul a wonderful companion. He has gained a sturdy foundation during the past 9 weeks, it will be up to his adopter to keep building on it.
Tobee is set to graduate at the end of December. If you would like to add him to your home, apply to meet him today!If you are not viewing this adoption listing from our website at www.bdar.org, please go there to get more information, find our adoption application, or submit an inquiry. Our pets are listed for adoption on multiple pet listing sites and we do not always have control over whether those sites are regularly or accurately updated. We also cannot guarantee we will receive forms or inquiries submitted through these 3rd party sites. For questions, call us at 307-514-4024.

animal.description: Beau Beau is a loving pup who will do anything for a belly rub. He loves a good walk and is quickly learning leash manners; however, he can still be a bit reactive to another barking dog, so needs quick redirection and is able to continue on his way. One of the first things you will notice is his award winning smile that will be sure to make you smile as well. He has shown no issues with eating dog food or drinking water, just a bit of extra drool/water slips out when he is excited. Beau Beau also has a one of a kind tail with a one of a kind wag. While it does not seem to slow him down or cause any pain, it does require a good clean-up from his humans after each time he goes potty as he has difficulty lifting his tail to get it out of the way completely. Having his butt shaved regularly has helped limit any mess and quicken the clean-up process. That being said, he knows the drill once the wipes come out and lays on his side, ready, but he is not always a fan and can become mouthy at times. Beau Beau is for sure still learning how to be a dog and appropriately show his love, but can become mouthy during clean-up time, when he is over tired, when he has some built up energy, and with other dogs. That being said, he has not shown aggression with the dog he lives with, he is just learning how to appropriately interact with other dogs, which will require patience from humans and dogs alike. He is working very hard to become the best dog he can be and knows commands such as: come, sit, leave-it, out, and down. He has been around polite children and has done fine on leash. On walks, he does seem to want to chase cats, so a home with cats would not be ideal. Beau Beau is crate trained and is able to spend the night in his crate and so far has been fine up to 6 hours / day in his crate, however he is a bit of an escape artist, so his crate needs just a bit of extra reinforcement. He eats separate from other dogs, however has shown no signs of food aggression or toy possessiveness. Speaking of toys, Beau Beau loves a comfy bed and a good bone to chew on. In cars, he does just fine, but if he had it his way, he would ride shotgun or in your lap as you drive as he thinks he is the perfect lap dog. Beau Beau would thrive in a house full of cuddles, patience, and belly rubs that is also able to continue training, teach him manners, and provide necessary structure. While nothing slows him down, he does need just a bit of extra help to stay clean and be the best pup he can!

Adoption Fee: $550 plus tax
**SPECIAL NEEDS**I would like to introduce you to Kaida. She is a special needs pup. She is happy and loving, but has some special medical needs and we are looking for that special foster or adoptive home that understands these needs and can give her a happy ever after.

See she had surgery before arriving to MN and although they tried, they did not fix her issue. We had her go to the U of M and they did a second surgery and fixed as much as they could but she will always have stool issues. They are much better and with a special diet and management, she can have a great life.

Here is what the U said at her check up: She continues to ooze some soft stool out of the right side of the rectum. ( This was present when tail lifted during exam) The mucocutaneous junction is healed but there is no anal sphincter palpable on the right side. She has two large poops daily and doesn't drop stool often until later on when softer stool oozes out of the right side ( about a 1/2 tablespoon. ) This needs to be cleaned off the perianal area otherwise it drops where ever she maybe standing.

Here is what she will need in her home: She need to be put on a low residue diet that only forms firm stool that is easier to clean up after and doesn't stick on her fur.

There is no surgical fix anymore. So we now need to find that special someone for this special girl.She is good with other dogs and kids. She does like to own her bones and food, so she will need to be worked with on that.Are you that special angel??

or

PETFINDER VIEWERS: Find our applications at www.midwestanimalrescue.org

*The pet you are viewing is a rescued pet which is most often from an animal control facility and does not come with a pedigree. The breed(s) listed are our best guess and are in no way guaranteed. Sometimes the pets appear to be a particular breed(s) in the pictures we receive from our rescue partners and when they arrive we are surprised to see an entirely different breed(s) in person! If you choose to DNA test your adopted pet, test results may vary from company to company and our breed guess may not be reflected in those results as it is just that, our best guess. It is with deep longing that we wish there was a breed called "cute" as we believe all of our dogs would fall under this new breed classification!

animal.description:
Sophie is a little white fluff of just 9 lbs. She is super sweet, friendly and well mannered. She adjusts quickly to new environments and gets along very well with her foster doggy siblings. 

She is playful and active, and 9 years old. Sophie likes to follow her humans around the house and she camps around her humans when her humans are stationary, working on the computer, watching TV… etc. 

Sophie is house trained at her foster home and she goes outside. Sophie is on the quiet side, but she has a loud voice when she barks. Sophie is slim even though she enjoys eating. Her favorite activity is going on walks. She walks well on leash and she walks pretty fast for such a small dog. She is kennel trained and she sleeps in her soft crate at night. Sophie follows instruction well. She  goes into her kennel voluntarily when asked and also she waits for an invitation before joining her humans at the couch or sitting in their laps. 

Before Sophie came to her current foster home, according to the vet, she had an ulcer in her right eye. It has since healed, but the scarring left a cloudy look on the eye. The cloudiness does not hinder her vision nor diminish her overall cuteness. She is very photogenic and especially adorable when she fashioned in her walking harness. She reminds of a miniature size  alpaca.

Sophie will be a wonderful pet and delightful addition to her future family. She has not been exposed to children under 10, so children in the home should be at least 10. 

Is Sophie's home with you?! 

She will need another dog in the home or someone that is home most of the time.  Children in the home need to be at least 10 years old.  She is located in S. TX

Donations are greatly appreciated for her care.  If would like to donate, please copy and paste this link into your browser:

https://donate.smallpawsrescue.org/

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please copy and paste this address in your browser: https://smallpawsrescue.org/pre-adoption-application/

To visit our home page, please copy and paste this address in your browser:  http://smallpawsrescue.org/

animal.description:
SAN MATEO COUNTY, CALIFORNIA

Meet Attila.  He is a 2 year old neutered male Anatolian Shepherd mix.  He currently weighs 87 lbs.

Attila has had a very rough life thus far.  He was likely discarded by a farmer in Iran, his country of origin, after  Attila had a broken leg.  He then became a street dog and had to scavenge in order
to stay alive.  His broken leg healed on its own, not in a perfect manner, but it does not interfere with Attila 's day to day life.  He is quite active and does not seem to have any major limitations.

Attila  was rescued by some very gracious, kind hearted people and made his way to California, where he is currently in foster care, awaiting adoption into his forever home.
He has been thoroughly vetted and is currently in good health.  As you can see from one of the pictures, it has been a long journey for him to regain his health and regrow his coat.

Attila  is good with both male and female dogs. He has not been evaluated with cats, livestock or small children.

Attila  is housebroken, walks on leash, knows basic commands and is good with both men and women.
Attila 's perfect home will be with a very kind, loving and patient person.  A low traffic home without young children is preferred.  Attila will do best in a home with another dog as a companion to him.

Attila is not available for long distance adoption.

Please contact us for more information on adopting this handsome gentleman.
asdrescue@gmail.com

animal.description:
Meet Megs! Our newest little misfit for our foster program has been here for about 6 weeks to work with her reactivity and overarousal issues. She's making some amazing progress here and is officially available to be shared for adoption! This itty bitty pittie mix is arguably the world’s cutest dog. Weighing in at 35lbs at a year old, she is a forever puppy. She has terrier tenacity, and the heart of a big dog in a small package.
Megs makes us laugh every day with her antics. While her personality in general is hilarious, she is also FUN. As you can guess from her size, this girl is agile and FAST. She has a ton of drive and will chase the flirt pole until she passes out. She also loves fetch and even hangs from the spring pole! She would be an amazing candidate for agility or fly ball. We also just recently started nose work and she is amazing at it. Because she is so biddable and food motivated, I even think she would enjoy something like rally obedience. She just wants to do stuff, and the specifics do not matter.
Megs has made vast improvements here. She has made so many human friends, and her barking at strangers is seemingly nonexistent now. She may be wary of new people at first, but it really does not take long to be in her inner circle. Once you are, she is a ball of love. Because of this nervousness, we do not want to send her to a busy city. Her former foster lives in New York and it was too much for her. We have acres here for her to run on, and she is happy as could be. Her “stranger danger” is relatively minimal at this point, and we would absolutely trust her in the hands of someone who understands how to do proper introductions and will continue appropriate socialization.
Megs has a ton of dog friends here. She is a rough and rowdy player and we have used her as our “tester” dog a few times. We had originally thought she was bombproof with dogs, but she has shown predatory behavior towards small dogs that we find concerning. We have tried to tell her that she herself is also a small dog, but she will hear none of that. We are not comfortable placing her in a home with a small dog but have very few concerns when it comes to larger dogs.
I hope the pictures are enough to sell someone on this ridiculous girl, but we also love having her here, and are not in a rush to place her with a set up that isn’t perfect. She is in Fairfield Connecticut currently but is available to anyone willing to travel. Contact Muddy Paws Rescue NYC for info on their adoption process and to take this little beast home. She's fully muzzle trained and has fantastic obedience!

Megs is spayed, microchipped and up to date on all age appropriate medical.  Please email adoptions@muddypawsrescue.org if you are interested in adopting Megs!

animal.description:
Are you an active, high energy family looking for a lifelong canine companion who can keep up with you?  Well then, look no further.  I’m Stormi, and I’m the one for you!

I’m 20 months old and I weigh 50 pounds. I’m a very smart, high energy, super affectionate dog and I don’t like to be away from my humans for long. I am so happy when you come home from your errands (or whatever it is that you do when you leave me).  I’ve got a big appetite and I will eat all my food as soon as you put it out for me.  Why, you ask?  Well, because I have a ton of energy! In my mind, I’m still a puppy. I love to run, run, run, both in the house and in the yard (if you don't believe me, watch the video). I definitely need a fenced-in yard, by the way. I love to chase balls, toys, and lizards. 

I’m learning my manners right now, because I’m very good with "sit" and "stay" in the house, but I’m not as obedient outside. I’m learning to walk well on a leash. 

If you would like to adopt me, please reach out to Safe Paws Rescue and we will send you an application to begin the adoption process. Safe Paws is a small rescue, so they accept inquiries from residents in Pinellas County only, please.

animal.description: Henry is a 1-2 year old Hound mix. Henry is loose, wiggly and happy! He likes to give gentle chin nudges and kisses. Like most hounds, Henry is high energy. This guy would need plenty of exercise in his life! He pulls on a leash but with some basic obedience training, this could easily be resolved. Henry is food motivated. Wow! knows the sit and shake command. He is not a fan of cats in a shelter atmosphere. Dogs are generally tested with dogs of their own size; and dog meets with the resident dogs are always encouraged. Our cat test should be used as a general purpose screening only to rule out overt aggression; we always recommend caution when introducing dogs to cats in the home. Recommendation on suitability of placement with children by their ages is based on behavioral observations including energy level and response to body handling. We never recommend leaving young children unsupervised with dogs, and we cannot guarantee the behavior of dogs with children, other pets or cats. Behavior evaluations should be considered as a snapshot of the behavior of the dog at this point in time; JHS believes all dog families need to be prepared to invest time and energy into training as well as provide common sense management of their new dog. We always encourage family to do some research on the breeds or mixes of breeds prior to adoption as many can have some unique characteristics that may or may not fit into their families. Always remember that the majority of dogs at our shelter have been exposed to or may have kennel cough. Kennel cough is contagious to other dogs, please talk to your vet if you have any questions about kennel cough prior to adoption. Please ask your adoption counselor at time of adoption if you have any unanswered questions regarding illnesses and treatments of the path that you are adopting. For more information about this dog or any others at our Shelter, please visit www.joplinhumane.org. We are the Joplin Humane Society in Joplin, Missouri. 417-623-3642 I AM SPONSORED! animal.description:
Bullet is a 7-month-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and working on housebreaking. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Ullie. I'm about 4 years old and 65lbs. 

Even though I had a hard life in Texas, I am thriving in a CO home with my foster humans and lab mix foster sister now. Im learning words like "sit" and "touch," trying to fit on every lap I can find for scratches, and love going for walks and play dates with other pups! I like other pups so much that I tug pretty hard on the leash when I see them and cant say hi, but Im responding really well to training (and cheese) and getting calmer every day. When I actually get to meet and play with dogs, I am super friendly and playful. I especially would love a home with a dog sibling my own size that appreciates my big and jumpy play style, but I would be able to ignore a dog sibling that wants none of that. Im a bit too interested in cats so would prefer a feline free home, and Im not sure how I feel about small children just yet, because Ive yet to meet any!

I dont like to brag but my inside manners are top notch. I haven't had any accidents, besides this one time I got a little confused by a potted plant but dont worry I have that figured out now! I also sleep great in a crate when peanut butter is involved but I am well behaved when left unattended outside of the crate too. Im medium energy so I love being a couch potato, but also would love a decent walk every day or hike once in a while.

If you are interested in adopting this sweet boy please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $250 includes the spay/neuter, vaccinations, deworming and microchip. 

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

Joaquin is such a sweet boy! He loves playing with other dogs. He has a moderately high energy level, but if you walk him daily and make sure he has chew toys, he enjoys spending a good portion of the day as a couch potato! Joaquin enjoys other higher energy dogs and enjoys a rough and tumble playtime. He gets nervous around men and needs slow intros to them. If Joaquin is around people that understand his need to come to them on his own terms, he will do great. Inside the home, he needed to be reminded of his manners when jumping but he is a dream. When walking, he will pull and is reactive to other dogs, so he will need continued training at his new home. Joaquin is a great snuggle buddy and he is so easy to fall in love with! His perfect furever family would be active each day!

animal.description:
Click my picture for more info. on me!
Meet Abby

Abby is a stunning 4 year old German Shepherd. This devoted girl has been with us for a few months going through heartworm treatment and is now ready to take applications.

Abby loves her people so much that she will need them to be home all day with her! She is a very smart eager to please lady and a major foodie. Abby is able to crate for short periods of time, house trained, knows commands and walks well on leash. While Abby loves having friends to play with she cannot be in a home with any small animals like cats, rabbits, or rodents. She has been working hard meeting other dogs on leash but will need a breed experienced owner that can commit to working on this more with her. Abby also requires a fenced back yard. She is a lovely lady who has brightened up any home she enters!

If you are interested in her, fill out an application at
www.fayettehumane.org/adopt/dogapplication

Due to COVID-19, we are not able to facilitate meet and greets until a family is approved and then only at the foster family's discretion. At this time, we are not holding dog adoptions at Petsmart.

**Applications can take anywhere from 5-7 business days to complete. When filling out an application, please scroll down after submitting it to be sure that the website accepted it and check for a confirmation email to be sure that your application went through. We respond by email, so please check your spam and trash folders.**

We are located in Fayette County, GA and are a foster based rescue without a shelter building.

Estimated DOB: 10/31/2016
Adoption fee: $350

CLICK HERE to APPLY TO ADOPT
or paste the following link in your browser: https://fayettehumane.org/adopt/dogapplication
For full details about ADOPTING, please visit our Adoption Guide (https://fayettehumane.org/adoption-information/adoption-guide/).

All our dogs are tested for heartworms, spayed/neutered, up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines and flea prevention.

Cats are tested for FLV/FIV when age appropriate, as kittens tested at an age less than 16 weeks tends to lead to unreliable results. All our cats are spayed/neutered, up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines and flea prevention.

animal.description:
I am currently in foster! If you would like to meet with me, please email my foster coordinator Abby at fostercoor@mckameyanimalcenter.org!

Dorita here is in need of a loving home with parents who are willing to help her learn that the world isn't so scary. She never got a chance to experience anything outside of the home she grew up in and came to us very scared. Dorita has now made wonderful improvements in her time here and is finally ready to have a real home! animal.description:
***Thanks to a generous supporter of our rescue, Fozzie's adoption fee is sponsored!***

Meet Fozzie!  This big handsome guy is a 2 year old terrier/mix who weighs in around 80+ lbs or so. Fozzie was adopted from our rescue when he was a puppy and his family adores him.  They reached out to us for help as there has been some major tension between Fozzie and his senior 4 legged sister.  They have worked with their vets and trainers and the conclusion is Fozzie would do best in a home without another dog.  The family is heartbroken over this but they want to make sure both dogs are living their best lives and are each in an environment they can thrive in.  Fozzie will be staying with his family for the time being while we work together to find him the best home.  

****

His family writes:

He is the best boy of all the good boys. Fozzie is the BIGGEST cuddle bug, and always needs to be cuddling someone. We’ve spoiled him and he sleeps with my son every night. He has crate anxiety from his rough start as a puppy, so we only put him in a crate if no one is home (he’s mischievous and likes to get into things when no one is around). He loves warm blankets, Kong chew toys, fresh bones from the butcher shop, peanut butter, any cuddles he can get, and any table scraps he can find (he is a counter surfer so if it’s left out on the counter...watch out! ?)

Fozzie loves to run and chase tennis balls, loves being on the trampoline, and wants to play with all the kids outside. We have 2 acres fenced in, so if his future family runs in public places he will definitely need lessons on manners while on a leash. He does not like to be outside if everyone is inside, and vice versa he doesn’t like being inside if everyone is outside. He is an amazing family dog. Fozzie is so good with all of our kids (ages 10,8, and 20 months). He is affectionate and loving with all of them, and enjoys cuddling with them on the couch or in bed. He loves to give slobbery kisses, but be forewarned his breath can be awful LOL!  Fozzie absolutely hates the outside hose, so when he gets into mud or dirt we have to throw him in the shower. Personally I think he just is boujee and likes the warm water. ? He won’t fight the bath, but he acts pretty dramatic during the whole event. Kids are no issue either, but he definitely needs space to get his energy out! I would also recommend a family who is ok with him being up on the couch, because he doesn’t know the meaning of personal space! ?

****

Fozzie is neutered, microchip, and current on all his vaccines.  He is an amazing boy and would be a great addition to an active, dog and cat free, home!  

Apply to adopt Fozzie today!

www.harleyshavendogrescue.com/adopt

animal.description:
Meet Anna! - the most joy you'll see on three legs anywhere! Anna is a darling, happy girl who's finally moving on from her terrible injury. Taken to the Garland Animal Shelter after being hit by a car, Anna was held for four days in terrible pain while the shelter waited for her owners to claim her. When no one did, we urged them to release her to us so we could save her leg. Unfortunately that wasn't possible and had to be removed.

Trust us here; it has NOT slowed her down in the slightest. Anna never meets a stranger, loves every body she meets and is ready for a walk or playing with another dog, when properly introduced. She's a high energy gal who'll benefit from a nice sized back yard and a playmate equal to her energy level. She's already crate trained and housebroken. She'll not do well crated long hours; e.g. 8 to 10 hours a day, she has way too much energy for that. But she'll make a loving and wonderful companion for any household willing to be her pack leader and focus her energies appropriately.

The stray hold, at the Toccoa-Stephens County Humane Shelter, is 5 days. That allows owners a fair amount of time to come looking for their pets. On the sixth day, the animal becomes the property of the Toccoa-Stephens County Humane Shelter and is offered for adoption. An animal may be pre-adopted, however, if the owner comes forward, within the 5 day stray hold, the animal goes back to the owner. The adoption fee is refunded at that time.
TSCHS Adoption Procedure
Adoption Fees: Adoption fee includes spay or neuter, current (age appropriate) vaccinations, and a microchip.
Hours of Operation:
 Tues.-Saturday, 11-6

Pricing:
 Dogs $100 - Puppies $125
 Senior dogs $60
 Cats $60 - Kittens $75
 Senior Cats $30

Contact Information:
Toccoa-Stephens County Humane Shelter
1747 Scenic Dr.
Toccoa, GA 30577
Phone: 706 282 3275
Fax: 706 886 7358
Email: Info@TSCHS.org

Adoption process:
 Fill out an application
 Fill out a contract
 Pay the adoption fee
*Stray animals may be Pre-adopted before the stray hold is up. If an owner comes forward, the adoption fee is returned to the adopter. If the owner does not come forward, the animal is scheduled to be altered. When that is done, the pet can go home with the adopter.
Unfortunately, we are not able to hold animals without the adoption process being completed.
That includes the payment of the adoption fee. Adoptions are done on a first come, first served basis. Applications can be emailed and payment can be made via phone and at WWW.PayPal.me/TSCHS.
Otherwise we can not hold animals. After the adoption fee has been paid, arrangements will be made to have the pet altered. No pets leave without being altered.

A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. If you have other dogs at home, tell the scheduler this because you should plan to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. animal.description:
Monaco is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Monaco is eligible for a foster to adopt. 

Age: ~2 years
Weight: ~70lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Takes some time to settle, but overall doing well with his crate-training. 
Dog sociability: Leash reactive (barks/lunges/pulls) at other dogs. He is strong and requires a confident handler.
Cat sociability: Not a match
Kids: Friendly with kids!
Ideal home: Monaco prefers to be a solo pet in a quiet neighborhood. He is not a match for a high-rise/elevator and would prefer a backyard!

Monaco is a big, silky love bug ready to steal your heart. He loves affection and craves cuddles, pets and kisses all day long. He's pretty calm in the home and likes to sunbathe in his favorite sun spots around the home or keep himself occupied with his toys. He's very well trained and his foster reports he even leaves the room when they are eating at the dinner table and doesn't beg. While he enjoys walks, he prefers to walk in quiet/calm areas where he won't encounter a bunch of other dogs. He has really loved his foster's backyard where he can take in all the smells and play. He will benefit from an adopter that will continue to work on training - he has come so far in a short amount of time and we know Monaco will only continue to build more confidence!

Monaco's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

animal.description:
This beautiful girl was just surrendered back to the rescue after nearly 3 years, the family fell on hard times and were unable to afford her minimal health care. Lexi is a 3 years old German Shepherd that needs daily medication for a condition that affects her pancreas. She is such a good sweet girl; she will do best in a home with older children. 

She knows several commands and loves people and other dogs. She is adjusting well in her new foster home. Such a gorgeous girl.

Here was her earlier story:

Looks at this beautiful, happy, lucky, sweet, fun little girl with floppy ears.You would never know what she had been through if we didnt tell you. But we want you to know so you too can appreciate the love and forgiveness of a dog. Anatasia was traumatized at only 4 months old. She was owner surrender to local shelter after being attacked by a dog. We think they may have tried to treat her but it was too expensive so they surrendered her to the local shelter where she had zero chance. She was rescued by Dallas Dogrrr so she could receive immediate vet care for her face; which required dental surgery and many stitches. They had to take a portion of the bottom of her mouth, and her skin was stretched on her top mouth to help heal. So she has an Elvis Presley grin (its pretty adorable); she is doing great now and is such a fighter. We hope we can find her a home that will love her forever and never give up on her.

animal.description:
MEET MONTGOMERY!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4506712.

To visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show. We have been told that you can go straight to the shelter and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog. From what we understand, the shelter will squeeze you in except between 12-3PM and near the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog. We hope your adoption process is smooth and full of happiness!

Montgomery was found on the street by a good samaritan and jumped in their car ready to go on his next journey. He was kept overnight and the finder stated he was potty trained and likes people. He is an energetic young boy that wags his tail constantly. He doesn't like his kennel very much and gets nervous when kennel staff or a volunteer comes to take him out of the kennel but once he is out, he is ready to GO!! He jumps up often and pulls on the leash and could definitely benefit from training to learn his manners. He would not do well in a home with small children because he is so energetic.

When Montgomery went to the play yard with other dogs, he went off by himself and didn't want to interact with them. When another dog approached him, he ran away from them. He wants to be on his own. When Montgomery was taken for a walk by a volunteer, he had on a cone due to his neuter surgery. The volunteer stated he was very easy to walk due to the cone so that shows he can learn.

If you think Montgomery would be a good fit in your home, then please bring the family and meet him today!!

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
Any questions or interest should be directed danitaskinsey@gmail.com. Remi is not at our shelter, so meet and greets should be planned with her family. Additionally, PAWS will cover a training consult with Hi-Line Canine, LLC if Remi's adopter is in our area. Triple Dog Brewing Co. has also graciously offered to sponsor her adoption fee. Please share this post so that we may cast a wide net for Remi. This is what her owner has to say about her:
Remi- I'm 8.5 yrs old, Born 6/5/2012. My birth mom was a border collie/blue heeler mix and dad was bull terrier.  
My lovable traits: I love men and especially  teenage boys teen boys are my favorite  Girls are ok too tho! I take a little bit to warm up sometimes (not normally) and I'm not super keen on strangers without a proper introduction. I've never been around little kids so probably a home without them would be best.  im very smart, loyal, and want to be by your side 24/7. The closer you are and more you touch me, the happier I am! I've been thru lots of training, however my grandpa has been very ill and mom has probably not had the time to keep me as brushed up on skills as I should be! Im really good on and off the leash, a great car rider/traveler. It's one of my favs! I also really love to go on a hike! 
The not so good traits: I absolutely do NOT tolerate other dogs.   My mom and dad who have had me since slightly shy of 4 weeks ( I was taken from my fur mommy way to young and my humans rescued me)  have worked really hard and I just won't give. I keep hurting my sisters to the point of vet visits.  I tolerate the cat however mom isnt sure I would if he were the only one around for me to "pick on".
Also, I was bit by a rattlesnale in 5/2018, which made me even more cranky than I was before. I have some tummy issues now and I require a more  sensitive tummy dog food. I've been eating lamb and rice from Sam's  Club  and doing pretty well, however i still have periods where i don't eat very well and I have some bouts of colitis. Not fun but after a couple days I am usually good to go again. 
I'm spayed and up to date on all my vaccinations. A fenced yard is a must for me.

animal.description:
Life on the streets wasn't real kind to to this sweet boy. He suffered a gash in his upper lip area that extends up to the nostril. But in spite of all he's endured, Clyfe is quiet, affectionate and appreciative of his human(s). Clyfe isn't trusting of other canines, and therefore he doesn't want to share his humans with them, so needs to be the only dog in his household. His big, soulful brown eyes seem to see all the way into your heart, and it's obvious that Clyfe has endured a lot in his 6 years and would so appreciate a kind, loving home.

*

*

Dogs in our foster care program are:

spayed/neutered

microchipped

up to date on all vaccinations

negative for heartworms and on regular heartworm preventative OR recently treated for heartworms and on regular heartworm preventative (It can take up to 6 months for a dog to test negative for heartworm after treatments. We will provide you all the medical documentation regarding the pet's treatment.)

NOT IN A SHELTER FACILITY. They are in loving foster care homes where they have received training and socialization to help them fit into your home more quickly. Therefore we schedule appointments in advance and do not have a general facility where you can view multiple dogs at one time.

Note about Breeds:

We do NOT do DNA tests on the dogs in our program. Many are found as puppies or young adults and we do not have any information about their parents. We select dog breed mixes based on recommendation from shelter staff and/or veterinarians and our experience in working with thousands of dogs. We consider the physical and behavioral traits of the dog as well as their size. If you are looking for a purebred dog and want to argue with us about breed standards, we encourage you to work with breed specific rescue organizations. If you are looking for a dog who have great personalities despite a mixed background (like most of us humans!), we'd love to work with you!

There are a few steps to set up the adoption.

Complete the
Adoption Application
online. Many dogs receive multiple applications and we review applications in the order they are received.

Foster will review your application and reach out to you to schedule a "virtual meet and greet".

Participate in a "virtual meet and greet".
This is a great way for you to get to see the dog in a setting where it is already comfortable and get lots of questions answered to determine if the dog's personality and energy level are a good fit.
This is also a great time to have a virtual "home visit" to show the fence, home, etc to minimize the amount of time the foster would need to come into your home later.

The foster and adoption coordinator will review the applications and notes from the virtual meet and greets and set up in person home visits with the applicants we feel are the best match for the dog's personality and energy level.

Trial Adoption -dogs are eligible for a trial adoption with the adopter that we feel is the best match. Trial adoptions last up to 3 nights and the foster will provide 3 days worth of food, information about the dog's schedule, and other tips and tricks to make it a successful transition. The adopt fee can be paid online as a deposit to start the trial adoption. If the dog is not the right fit, we refund the adoption fee.

As a 100% volunteer-powered organization, we appreciate your patience as we review the applications.

animal.description:
My name is Nyla and I had a forever home as a pup and they decided they no longer wanted me...so I was given to a friend...and after about a year...things have changed for all of us...She is no longer able to give the time and attention that I need.

I am about 3 yrs old..up to date on my vaccines, microchipped and spay. I was heartworm positive, but only adults no microfilaria and am on monthly heartworm preventative, (the only think deadly about heartworms if nothing is done).
I am housebroken and crate trained... . My adoption fee is $250.00.

I have a unique look ...my tail is shorter than most due to the fact that my mom chewed my tail off as a pup. Why?? Who knows...but someone was obviously not paying attention to mom and pups. 

I am the alpha and bond with my people...I will get used to another dog in the house, but am very dominate and bossy with that dog. Therefore.. I will be the Alpha dog and this can cause issues and my person can do nothing about that. Dogs establish their own pecking order and it just is the way it is.  I am also super smart, I know how to open doors, so my family should be prepared for my intelligence, hence the reason a seasoned, experienced Shepherd family is the be match for all me. My last parent said I could open doors..so please consider this. 

I love to run, so will need regular exercise. I also need a 6 ft+ wooden fence as I am able to climb a chain link. Shepherds are high shedders ...12 months a year..so some maintenance on your part will be required. There are a lot of good de-shedding shampoos and there is also a new food out that cuts down on the shedding and dander.

There is an application process and a home visit WILL be required. Your location is not an issue, we can get the home visit done.

WHEN ADOPTING A PET, KEEP IN MIND IT CAN BE A 15++ YEAR COMMITTMENT. PLEASE ADOPT RESPONSIBLY!!

animal.description: Stitch is an approximately two-year-old (maybe younger), 40-lb Australian Cattle Dog and German Shepherd mix currently being fostered in Homosassa, FL (Citrus County). Stitch is loyal and likes to be with his person full time. Stitch loves to play all day with toys and other dogs! He has an extremely strong prey drive and needs a job with LOTS and LOTS of activity and exercise. Stitch needs an extremely active family who will give this boy an outlet for his energy. Because of his energy level and playful personality, a family with another ACTIVE and younger dog would be best for him. T he ideal place for him would be a farm or rural area, with lots of space, a job and/or other dogs to play with, and little traffic to chase vehicles. He's not an apartment dwelling dog and also not one to be left all day crated. Stitch is partially deaf but can hear high whistles and low engine rumbles. H e knows some hand signals, including sit and come. He is crate trained and will stay in his crate at night or during the day when unattended. He can bark a little bit when left alone, but he calms down quickly. Because he can easily be distracted, he needs a safe place from vehicles. Stitch requires a home with a fenced in yard. He is house trained, crate trained, neutered, and up to date on vaccines.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Diffie! I was named after the late and great Joe Diffie. I am a VERY sweet guy, but boy, am I big and goofy. I think I am a lap dog because, well, aren’t I?! I love to snuggle and give hugs, and follow you through the house. I am doing really well with my potty training, and know how to use a dog door. I am also crate trained. I love to be active! I could be the perfect hiking partner if you’ll have me. I am learning how to walk like a gentleman on a leash.
Although I was raised with cats and children from the time I was just a little pup, I do forget my size and strength sometimes and can overwhelm the little beings. My littlest foster brother is working on slow and calm movements because my puppy brain is super reactive to fast and loud things, and my foster mom is teaching me my manners and how to stay calm when those sneaky kittens dart across the floor. I am very food motivated. With continued training, I might do really well in a house with smaller children and cats, but my foster mom says it might be in my best interest if my kids were older and my cats were older and dog smart, or if there just were no cats. I do really well with other dogs and will prefer a family that has another big dog for me to play with.
My foster mom wants you to know that I am extremely adorable, but I will be HUGE. I am only 4.5 months old and already almost as big as my boxer sister at 46lbs. Please take my size into consideration when making the decision to bring me into your family.**

animal.description:
It is JUST JACK! This is a miracle boy, we pulled him from the euthanasia room, needle in paw, and we are sooooooooo happy that we were able to save this exceptional happy, wiggly pup.

Jack is very sweet and cuddly who likes other dogs, as long as they don't challenge him. He LOVES kids, we mean he would be the perfect nanny, he is not such a fan of cats or farm animals. His ideal home would be active, would best as an only dog, but could possibly live with a low energy, submissive female dog.

Jack was a stray from the street and when we got him he was lacking manners, so he went into intensive boot camp training to make him ready for his new family. He has been a superstar at training camp, we are talking Brady level superstar.

He has spent the last month with a trainer and he is doing so well and is definitely a country dog, except for ponies, he does not like ponies...Jack has mastered the art of relaxation, playing with other pups, walking well on a leash, snuggling, and has learned to live life off the streets. We are hoping to find him a home that is in the suburbs, no small animals, no ponies, no cats, but bring on the dogs, he loves dogs, playing, romping, roughhousing, but knows when to stop. 

Jack has come so far and is ready for us to find him the best home ever. A meet and greet with him and our trainer will be required. We cannot wait for you to meet this incredible boy, you will fall in love in an instant as we all have.

animal.description:
BAM! You just got hit with the Ming stickotherwise known as the OMG, so stinking adorable you might pass out stick.
Can we just say 1/2 Fireball 1/2 Comedian all wrapped up in an adorable cuddle bug?
Seriously, folks, we're not joking here!
He will keep you laughing with all his silly, playful antics.
Ming is a most adorable young pittie mix who is about 2 years old if that and weighs around 50 lbs making him a bit of an itty pittie.
That being said, he could use a few more as he is very lean and needs to pack on a few. Best way to describe him is that Ming is everything a human teenager is not. He is friendly, outgoing, loves to see and engage with anything on two or four legs, will never roll his eyes at you, and will always think you are the best thing since sliced breadand can't we all use a little bit of that adoration?! Ming is a good boy who is learning so many things at the farm and showing himself a grade A student. Ming is eager to please and treat motivated. He knows "sit" and "stay" with the help of a treat, does well on walks, has excellent potty habits, and is crate trained.
He is eager to learn and show his smarts too so training will just become a fun game he plays with everyone to show how smart he really is.

He would love an active family and would likely do quite well with playmates, he loves the ladies, in particular, that like to romp and roll as much as he does but would seriously be fine being an only dude. He equally loves to cuddle up with his humans and is great with older kids.
Ming is just too much cuteness so someone best come pick him before our hearts explode!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Dear Santa Paws,

It's me, Shirley, and I'm not a baby anymore! Do you remember me from last Christmas? I was only 3 months old then! But now that I'm a big girl, and I know how to write, I thought I would send you a letter to let you know what a crazy year it's been! You'll never believe this, but over the summer, I went on a wild adventure. Remember how I was living in Tennessee? Well some nice people put me on a big huge van, and now I live in New York! So please make sure when you bring me my presents, you come to the right house, okay?

I have been SUCH a good girl this year, you don't even know! I don't make a peep in the night so that my foster family can get lots of sleep! I know not to go potty in the house anymore, like when I was a puppy, because that would make my hoomans very sad. I am sweet, kind, and gentle with everybody - I just LOVE PEOPLE - and I have been super generous with my kisses, snuggles, and tail wags all year long. Also, have you been watching me playing with my doggy friends? Haven't I been amazing? I'm still your happiest, silliest, clumsiest girl! But hey, what do you expect with such long limbs and floppy ears like mine? OH! Another thing! I always notice when stuff is left out and about, and I sniff those stuffs with my awesome hound nose just to check them out, and yes, I get excited about those stuffs, but I ONLY sniff them, Santa, I swear, I NEVER chew on the stuffs because I know I shouldn't! And you know what? That is REALLY hard because I'm a dog, and I want to chew on all the things! But I don't, see? What did I tell you? I have been the very best girl there ever was!

I know this might be a lot to ask, but the only thing I REALLY want this year, Santa, is a family of my own. Since you have magic Christmas spirit power, is this something you think you could do? If you can, here is my wish list: a big or bigger-than-me doggy sibling who will play outside with me for hours and hours, maybe some hooman kids who will play fetch and run around the yard with me, and people who will snuggle me forever on the couch and give me LOTS of pets and kisses, and will be patient and kind with me. Oh, and a family who is home a lot! Is that possible? I know I'm a year old now, and this is kind of embarrassing, Santa, but I'm still scared of so many things, and I don't want to be left home alone all day. I hope you understand, and that maybe you might have the perfect family in mind for me? Please? Also, do families fit down the chimney? Do you stuff them down one at a time? How does it work? Well, I know you'll figure it out, Santa! I believe in you!

Woofs and kisses,
Your favorite girl, Shirley

Apply to meet Shirley

**MUST BE ADOPTED TO A HOME WITH ANOTHER DOG**

animal.description:
Meet Takola -

If you’re looking for the perfect addition to your active home, your search is over because Takola is your boy! This lovable weirdo is a 8mo Shepard mix and has been the life of the party since arriving at his foster home. This boy just wants to be loved and is always looking for ways to prove he’s a good boy. He will have you belly laughing at his puppy antics and quirky personality! And if you’re looking for a running buddy? Takola's your boy!  He is doing an awesome job going on 3-4 mile runs!

Takola is completely house broken and mostly crate trained. Overnight he’s been doing great sleeping in his crate, and even likes to sleep in past his humans some mornings. He does still need a bit of reinforcement that he’s going to be okay when his humans leave and that they will always return to give him more love, but with time, this smart boy will learn this as well. With his high energy breed, he does need to go to a home with a fenced in yard for him to run and get out some of his energy. Takola loves playing with other playful fast dogs and enjoys meeting new dogs.  A playful dog friend is a prefect match thus he is a wonderful 2nd playful dog!  Takola needs to go to a home with another dog to help him be ok when alone.   This boy is so intelligent and wants to please- training and obedience class will be so fun with him!  He will learn your routine quickly and adapt accordingly. In the short time he has been here, he has already learned sit, stay, and “on-by” while out on runs.

Takola does great with new people and older kids, but does need a reminder  that not everybody wants to get a hug from him right away. He loves to meet other new pups though and will have you giggling as he romps around with an ear to ear smile on his face!  While another dog is not a requirement for this boy, it could help him adjust a little easier and would provide a nice buddy for him to play and run off his energy with. He is also good with cats. He may chase here and there if they take off, but if he catches up to them, you’ll just find him tilting his head and trying to make friends. As with any high energy breed, he may be a little active at first, but a little training and loving reassurance will have him snuggled on the couch with you in no time.

Takola  just wants to be loved and have fun.  If you are looking for an active adventure buddy and a dog who will make you laugh and love- Takola is your guy!
If you would like to meet Takola, please visit spotslaststop.org and fill out an application.

animal.description:
Loving, playful & affectionate, everyone meet our #Queen #WiggleButt Ms. #Nala. She's 4 years old, 55lbs, and an American Staffordshire Terrier mix. At the end of the day, Nala is honestly just the biggest lover that you'll ever meet. Nala craves human companionship, loves her daily walks, enjoys sunbathing in the backyard, lives for belly rubs, she's all about cuddles & movie nights & loves to give big kisses. She's 100% potty trained, 100% crate trained and does well on a leash.  Nala knows all of her basic commands and is very eager to please. The perfect family for Nala would be one that is active, loves the outdoors, an avid runner or someone who loves going on daily walks, and definitely a family that loves cuddles & puppy kisses.

When it comes to people, Nala loves everyone she meets! She loves & adores children and would make the perfect family pet. She'd do best in a home with kids over 10 years of age because at times she doesn't always understand her strength. Nala would thrive best as the only dog in her furever home, although she has made a few friends while in our care. Nala does not do well with female dogs,  but does well with submissive male dogs with a proper introduction. But once again, we would like her to be the only dog in her forever home. Nala absolutely adores the cat that is currently in her foster home- especially when it comes to cuddle time.

Adoption Requirements: No Exceptions
- Fenced in Yard Required
- Needs to be the ONLY DOG in her new home
- Nala would thrive best as the only dog in the home, but does do well with most submissive male dogs & does great with the male cat in her current foster home

Want To See More Pics:
https://www.petfinder.com/dog/nala-50060051/mi/ferndale/pro-pet-otic-foundation-mi1050/

Nala is currently up for adoption through Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue located in Metro Detroit. Her adoption fee is $150  & will include her distemper, rabies, bordetella, parvo, & lepto vaccines; deworming; microchip; heartworm test; fecal test & being fixed. Nala is currently on both flea & tick prevention and has had her ProHeart 6 Injection for heartworm prevention. 

***PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE POST & FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS****

Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue; previously known as the PRO-PET-OTIC Foundation, is a 100% Foster-Based Rescue that is ran by all Volunteers. Which means that we are not a shelter & each animal is in an actual home with a foster family. We kindly ask that you put any questions within the email & our team of Volunteers will get back to you. With the overwhelming amount of emails please be patient with our 100% volunteer family and we will get back to you. The application MUST BE filled out, a Vet Check MUST BE completed by our team, as well as a phone interview before we do a 'Meet N Greet.'
 
How To Apply:
If you're interested in adopting one of our available dogs:
1. Email LendingaHelpingPaw313@gmail.com with the dogs name as the subject when you ask for the adoption application.
2. Once you have completed the application, please print it out, fill it out, scan it, & then email it back to LendingAHelpingPaw313@gmail.com. If you do not have a scanner, please take a picture with your phone and we kindly ask that you sent all attachments into one email.
3. Please make sure to call your vet to grant our organization permission to do a vet check on your current pet.
4. If you are interested in more than one dog, please list your top 3 choices on the completed application.
5. Please be honest & truthful on your application. We always do a vet Check. We always do a home visit. And we always have both the prospective families & dogs best interest at heart!

Thank you in advance for all of your love & support,
The Lending A Helping Paw Dog Rescue Family

animal.description: Delilah came to us from Pinellas County Animal Services, where she had spent several months recovering from some head and torso wounds. Delilah quickly became a staff favorite at the shelter and won the hearts of many when she smiled! You see, we all think that Delilah was used for fighting (as a "bait" dog)-not because she wanted to fight, but because she is so sweet. Delilah was picked up as a stray with many puncture wounds across her face and torso. Her fur has grown in white where her scars used to be. Delilah was at first, frightened of female doggies, and was also a bit uncertain of the male ones too. She has since warmed up to most male dogs and will play with them in a rough and tumble, but nice way. She will also now walk past a female dog without incident, and is learning many new commands and tricks! Delilah spends time lying around in the sun on the sand, chasing tennis balls, and tossing around her favorite rope toys. She takes treats gently and has nice leash manners as well. Delilah still has a lot of "puppy energy" and likes to chew. She is learning not to use her mouth to get attention, but rather to sit patiently and wait for a treat. If you fell in love with Delilah's sweet face, heard her sad story, and have the heart and the patience to continue with her training, please visit our online application to meet sweet Delilah!

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Jersey! I'm a fun-size 1-year-old pocket bully mix. I have been through so much in my one year of life. I have bounced between 4 homes; life has been so hard. Due to this instability, I have developed some inappropriate behaviors, such as nipping at new people's feet when I get too excited. I have been experiencing some severe separation anxiety here at the shelter, but I'm hoping that will go away when I find a loving home that can provide the structure I desire. I think I am a one-owner kind of gal. I get very attached to my people, and I want to be the most important thing in their lives!! I will require an adopter who is experienced in owning pups like me who could use some behavior modification help! I do best when I'm kept occupied. Exercise and games are the best! I loooove chasing balls in the yard or hanging out on the couch gnawing on a good chew toy. Having some rules and boundaries would help too. I just want to be a productive member of society! I can be a little fearful when meeting new people, so I would appreciate if you toss me treats from a distance and let me approach you on my own terms. I have played in doggie play groups, but I can be a bit too much sometimes, so I would do best in a home as the only dog. In my forever home, I could do without kids. But as long as they are old enough to understand my needs, then I'm sure we can make it work! If you think my smooshy face is super cute, you should come meet me at Stray Haven!! We can see if we would be a good match!
Stray Haven Humane Society & SPCA
194 Shepard Rd., Waverly, NY 14892
(607) 565-2859, www.strayhavenspca.org 
Open hours (winter): Tues, Wed & Thurs Noon - 6pm; Sat 10am-4pm

animal.description:
Aurora is a 1 year old Boxer mix weighing 55 pounds. She came to us as a stray so her history is unknown. Aurora is anything but sleeping beauty! While this girl is very pretty, she is VERY high energy! She is full of boxer puppy energy and would benefit from a very active home to work out that energy and build her confidence. She is very sweet and loves attention, she gives the best kisses in exchange for belly rubs. Her favorite things are squeaky toys and peanut butter! She knows commands sit and shake. She absolutely loves walks but needs a lot of work on a leash and her manners. She is a jumper so a family with no small children is required. She will benefit from training classes. She's extremely treat motivated but can be distracted easily. She also thinks she is a lap dog!

Her adoption fee is $250, this includes her spay, heartworm test, vaccines current, deworming, heartworm/flea prevention and micro chipped. Her dog license is also required to be purchased for Sandusky County residents at time of adoption, which is an additional $20.75. 

Please visit the shelter to meet her, we show dogs Monday through Friday 1-4:30pm and Saturday 1-3:30pm. Please note, we do not offer same day adoptions.Come and meet your new best friend today! The Humane Society of Sandusky County is open Monday -Friday 1pm - 5pm and Saturdays from 1pm - 4pm. Also, be sure to check us out on FaceBook!

animal.description:
Zara is a spayed young Staffy/Boxer mix. She is about 2-3 years old. She is the mother of Jesse, Cary, and Randy.

Here's what her foster mom has to say about her!

""Zara is doing good. She's a 50-pound super ENERGETIC puppy pretty much! She wants to play all the time and loves nothing more than her toys! She seems to be adjusting better with our dog as well. There haven't been any snapping incidents since that first week, but we are also very diligent about watching her with treats and bones and toys so both dogs have their space. She probably should have some basic obedience training, because she's got that like bully breed in her and can be stubborn. It will also teach her not to jump up or at people. She does know sit and down, and will do so with treats, but you have to be very firm with her. Playtime is her favorite time, as she loves to play tug of war and often will have multiple toys in her mouth. She's definitely got a great personality about her and loves to give doggie kisses while sitting on your lap.

We are working on leash training, and that will just take some time. Walks are fun and very good for her since she's got tons of energy! She sniffs the ground the whole time. She might do great as a running partner, but we have to get her trained to walk nicely on a leash first. She is unsure of new people and new environments and will bark at people she doesn't know, but the people we've had come over she's been okay with as long as she sees them enter the house. We've also gotten her used to being in the crate during the day and at night. She should do great with older kids, like pre-teen and up, since they can play with her all the time, but younger kids might accidentally get knocked over. She does okay with our cats, but will chase after them if they run.""

1-20-21 Update: ""She's been doing fine, lots of kisses and tail wagging and tug of war! We are still working on getting her used to walking on a leash (with and without a harness). She needs some more confidence since everything is ""new"" to her, but she's learning, and definitely a lover and a very sweet puppy.""

If you are interested in meeting Zara, please fill out an application on our website: https://us01.sheltermanager.com/service?account=ah0334&method=online_form_html&formid=5To complete an adoption application, go to: http://almosthomeanimals.org/applications/adoption/

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Bella Sue. Are you looking for a spunky senior gal who will love you forever? Then I'm your girl! Before coming to ARNO, I was in a terrible hoarding situation. When they found me, I had no hair on most of my body. You would never know that I had a ruff start to life because I'm such a friendly girl.

Since then, I've been enjoying the good life at my foster home and now my beautiful red coat is growing back! I'm housetrained, not destructive indoors, and people friendly - I have liked every stranger I've met (they aren't strangers to me! Just more people who can give me some lovin' ). I love playing with squeaky toys, snuggling on the couch and sunbathing outside. My name may be Bella Sue but it should've been Dora the Explorer because I love going on adventures. Every time my foster mom grabs my leash to go on a walk, I do a happy dance.

Won't you come meet me? I promise you won't regret it. You'll fall in love with my affectionate personality and adorably wrinkly forehead. I cannot wait to find my fur-ever home soon!

________________________________________________


My adoption fee is $200. This includes a spay/neuter, up-to-date vaccines, deworming, a microchip, a heartworm test, and, if needed, heartworm treatment.

________________________________________________

For all animals that have not been spayed or neutered a $100 deposit will be required in addition to the adoption fee. The deposit is refundable upon completion of the spay / neuter surgery.

For more information email: adopt@animalrescueneworleans.org.

To complete an application, please visit: https://animalrescueneworleans.org/adoptfoster/.

Please visit our facebook for more information about adoption specials, and adoption events. Events are a great way to meet multiple animals at a time!

animal.description: Richie is a great dog...possibly a Shepherd/lab mix. He's friendly, ok with kids and other dogs. His one "flaw"? We suspect that once he is in a new home, TIME, CONSISTENCY, and PATIENCE will pay off and help this boy overcome his desire to see what is on the other side. As we said, he's a great boy, affectionate, playful, and exuberant, and with a little bit of work, he's going to be a fantastic companion to a family for the rest of his life! Come meet this boy!

animal.description: Meet BB, the most resilient and happy dog you will ever meet. Her heart warms up to every human and dog instantly and she just loves hearing her name. Her tail will wag the second she hears your voice and will come to you and stay by your side. She loves getting pets, cuddles, and attention so much so, that her eyes will close in absolute bliss when you pet and cuddle her. She loves putting her head on your leg or chest just to be near you. You can truly feel the love and appreciation she has to give every day. BB needs a home that has calm animals since she is partially blind. She needs someone who will be dedicated to her health improvement, which includes a strict diet, and a little bit of exercise. She is okay in a crate but has no anxiety if left alone. She will just wait by the door until you come back. She is a champ taking her insulin shot in the morning and will gobble up any food you give her. BB is a bundle of joy and love and you cannot help but be inspired by her positivity. She makes you feel so loved and appreciated and would be the perfect addition to any home. In a nutshell, BB is SWEET; HAPPY; LOVING; CUDDLY; CALM; QUIET; HUNGRY; PATIENT; RESILIENT. This pet is available for pre-adoption and may not be officially ready for adoption, as it is still undergoing medical treatment. Depending on the medical status, a Meet and Greet may be put on hold until they can safely participate in a meeting with potential adopters. In some cases, this pet may be able to move to its forever home while it is still under the medical care of Dallas Pets Alive. If you are interested in learning more, apply now and one of our Adoption Counselors will discuss the options available so you can bring home your new furry family member! Applications are processed in the order in which they are received; please be aware that this pet may have interested applicants ahead of you. All Dallas Pets Alive adoptable pets are spayed or neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines upon adoption. The standard minimum donation for dogs over six months to seven years is $200, puppies under six months is $250, dogs eight years and over are $100 unless specified otherwise. You can view all adoptable pets and fill out an adoption application online on our website at http://dallaspetsalive.org/adopt/adoptable-dogs/ . For more information, you can email adopt@dallaspetsalive.org.
